subSubSection.paragraph:
New material deposited in the Limnological Institute of Irkutsk, Siberian Branch of the Academy of Sciences (
LISB
).

Locality. Lake Baikal, Southern basin, Murino bank;
51 ° 30 ’ 07” N
,
104 ° 29 ’ 06” E
);
25–27 September 1997
; at 18 m depth (net sampling); sandy sediment with big separate stones obstructing dredging or grabbing.

Geographical distribution and habitat.
To date, only known from Lake Baikal, Maloye More (Olkhonskiye varota) and Murino bank (southern basin; 
18 m
), both localities +/- 
250 km
from each other.
